related_questions.question: Is white bread healthy to eat?
related_questions.snippet: When is bread not healthful? The highly processed flour and additives in white, packaged bread can make it unhealthful. Consuming too much white bread can contribute to obesity, heart disease, and diabetes. However, buying bread with the word “whole” as the first ingredient still does not guarantee a healthful product.

related_questions.question: Is white flour bread healthy?
related_questions.snippet: White, refined flour produces a bread which is quick and easy to digest. Eaten regularly and in high amounts, foods like this may lead to weight gain and an increased risk of metabolic conditions such as type 2 diabetes and heart disease.
related_questions.title: Is bread healthy? - BBC Good Food

related_questions.question: Why do athletes eat white bread?
related_questions.snippet: Foods rich in unrefined carbohydrates, like wholegrain breads and cereals, should form the basis of the athlete's diet. More refined carbohydrate foods (such as white bread, jams and lollies) are useful to boost the total intake of carbohydrate, particularly for very active people.

buttons.subtitle: Is White Bread Healthy
buttons.title: White Bread: Is it Good or Bad for Your Health? - ZOE
buttons.snippet: White bread is a processed food with low-quality carbs. Plus, it can contain added sugar. So, eating white bread can cause large blood sugar spikes, which aren't good for your health. For the remaining 45% of people, it's OK to enjoy white bread in moderation — around 2 or 3 times a week.

buttons.subtitle: What Does White Bread Do To The Body
buttons.title: New research suggests that eating sliced white bread be as dangerous ...
buttons.snippet: Numerous studies show how recurring blood-sugar spikes from eating high-glycaemic white bread can increase the risk of type 2 diabetes and obesity, as well as heart disease. According to data published in the journal Diabetes Care, white bread has a glycaemic index (GI) of 75.
